<item>
            <title>[LU-10549] Cannot start lnet with MOFED 3.4</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10549</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since commit 31d6445718b896290198f5d127f86c174d499c6c, we are unable to load lnet when using MOFED 3.4&lt;br/&gt;
[  816.546805] LNetError: 28107:0:(o2iblnd.c:2519:kiblnd_hdev_get_attr()) Invalid mr size: 0x3fdf&lt;br/&gt;
[  816.548804] LNetError: 28107:0:(o2iblnd.c:2739:kiblnd_dev_failover()) Can&apos;t setup device: -22&lt;br/&gt;
[  816.550756] LNetError: 28107:0:(o2iblnd.c:2849:kiblnd_create_dev()) Can&apos;t initialize device: -22&lt;br/&gt;
[  817.552196] LNetError: 105-4: Error -100 starting up LNI o2ib&lt;br/&gt;
[  817.555577] LustreError: 28107:0:(events.c:630:ptlrpc_init_portals()) network initialisation failed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This seems to be related to the (changing) position of the ib_device-&amp;gt;attr field. The position of this field is different in lustre (due to odp_statistics being zero-lenghted) and mofed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lustre should not ignore the (M)OFED options when --with-o2ib is specified on build.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
